definitions.definition: the univalent anion HCO 3 ; any salt of carbonic acid in which only one of the hydrogen atoms has been replaced.
Sodium bicarbonate used as a mild antacid ; bicarbonate of soda .

main_definition: ( organic chemistry ) the univalent anion HCO 3 ; any salt of carbonic acid in which only one of the hydrogen atoms has been replaced. [from 1814]
